            "widgets_values": [
              "",
              "CRITICAL RULES:\n- COMPOSITION LOCK: The output must be a pixel-accurate recreation of the source image's layout. Every subject must be in the same position, same pose, same scale, same cropping. Do not reframe, recompose, or reinterpret the scene in any way.\n- SUBJECT FIDELITY: All people, objects, and environmental elements from the source image must be present and recognizable. Faces must retain their identity, expression, and gaze direction. Body positions, hand placements, and clothing must match exactly.\n- ENVIRONMENT PRESERVATION: Architecture, furniture, objects, background elements, spatial depth, and perspective must remain identical to the source image. Only their visual rendering style changes.\n- STYLE APPLICATION: Apply the described style treatment uniformly across the entire image — color palette, lighting quality, texture, mark-making, edge treatment, and atmospheric mood must match the style description. The image should look as though the original scene was captured or created using the described medium and technique from the start.\n- NO CONTENT CHANGES: Do not add, remove, move, or alter any element from the source image. Do not change the time of day, weather, or environmental conditions unless the style description explicitly implies it (e.g., a \"golden hour warm tone\" style may shift color temperature but not scene geometry).\n\nThe output should look like the source image was re-created from scratch in the described style — same scene, same moment, completely different visual treatment.",
              ""
            ]
